org.jmisb.api.klv.st1108.st1108_3

Class WindowCornersPack

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jmisb.api.klv.st1108.st1108_3.WindowCornersPack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKlvValue, IInterpretabilityQualityMetadataValue

    public class WindowCornersPack
extends Object
implements IInterpretabilityQualityMetadataValue
    Window Corners Pack.

    From ST 1108.3:

    The Window Corners Pack, which is a defined length pack (DLP), describes a sub-image region within an image Frame for the metric calculation bounded by Frame Line[start] to Frame Line [end] and Frame Row[start] to Frame Row[end].

    This enables defining a local region within an image to calculate image metrics rather than over the entire image.

    The Window Corners Pack is optional. If not provided, the metrics are assumed as taken over the entire image.

      • WindowCornersPack

        public WindowCornersPack(int c1row,
                         int c1column,
                         int c2row,
                         int c2column)
        Create from values.

        The values essentially provide a bounding box defined by [c1row, c1column] as the upper left hand corner, and [c2row, c2column] as the lower right hand corner.

        Values are zero based, in units of pixels.

        Parameters:
        c1row - starting row (top row for the region of interest)
        c1column - starting column (left hand column for the region of interest)
        c2row - ending row (bottom row for the region of interest)
        c2column - ending column (right hand column for the region of interest)
